{title: Be Not Afraid}
{artist: Daniel O'Donnell}
{composer: Written by Felix Mendelssohn}

And [C]I will [D7]give you [G]rest
[D7]If you [G]pass through raging [D7]waters
In the [Em]sea you [D7]shall not [G]drown
If you [C]walk amid the burning flames
[Am]You shall not be [D7]harmed
If you [G]stand be[B7]fore the [Em]power of [Dm]hell
And [C]death is [A7]at your [D7]side
[G]Know that [Em]I am [Am]with you through it [D7]all
Repeat #2
Blessed are the [D7]poor
For the [Em]kingdom [D7]shall be [G]theirs
[C]Blessed are you that weep and mourn
For [Am]one day you shall [D7]laugh
And if [G]wicked [B7]men in[Em]sult and [Dm]hate you
[C]All be[A7]cause of [D7]Me
[G]Bless[Em]ed  [Am]blessed are [D7]you
Repeat #2